Gill-exopod formula typical for genus (see
Miya 1980
;
Berggren 1991
); no rudimentary exopod visible on basis of P 1 .

Etymology. Specific name derived from the Greek sauros (neo-Latin
saurus
) for “lizard”, in reference to Lizard Island, the type locality.

Habitat. Sand flat with large coral heads and coral rubble, at depth of about 1 m ; associated with unknown burrowing hosts, possibly Callianassidae or Echiura (see
Berggren 1991
).
